text:
Gravesend Bay, at the foot of 21st Ave., showing a break water encircling a portion of the Bay, that will eventually be filled in and have Warehouse Ave., extended thereon. View 1, shows homes numbered 1916-1962 on Cropsey Ave. at the present shore line. Shortly they will be two blocks inland. Nos. 2 and 3 are westward and show the encircling stone barrier.

April 27, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Gravesend Bay - Brooklyn - 21st Street.

text:
Coney Island Creek, east from West 21st Street to the Cropsey Ave. Bridge and showing both sides of the Creek. View No. 2 is from the foot of West 20th Street on the south bank.
May 17, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.
